# Building an NPM Package for React Icon Components

Since you already have your icons as React components saved as `.js` files in an `icons` folder, let's adapt the process to create an NPM package for these specific assets.

## 1. Set Up Your Project Structure

```
my-react-icons/
├── icons/              # Your existing React icon components (.js files)
├── src/                # Source code
│   └── index.js        # Main entry point
├── package.json
├── README.md
├── .gitignore
└── .npmignore
```

## 2. Initialize Your Package

```bash
mkdir my-react-icons
cd my-react-icons
npm init
```

Answer the prompts to create your `package.json` file.

## 3. Configure Your Package.json

```json
{
  "name": "my-react-icons",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "My custom React icon components",
  "main": "dist/index.js",
  "module": "dist/index.esm.js",
  "files": [
    "dist"
  ],
  "scripts": {
    "build": "rollup -c",
    "prepublishOnly": "npm run build"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "react": "^16.8.0 || ^17.0.0 || ^18.0.0",
    "react-dom": "^16.8.0 || ^17.0.0 || ^18.0.0"
  },
  "keywords": ["icons", "react", "components"],
  "author": "Your Name",
  "license": "MIT"
}
```

## 4. Install Development Dependencies

```bash
npm install --save-dev rollup @rollup/plugin-node-resolve @rollup/plugin-babel @rollup/plugin-commonjs rollup-plugin-peer-deps-external @babel/core @babel/preset-env @babel/preset-react
```

## 5. Create a Rollup Config

Create a `rollup.config.js` file:

```javascript
import resolve from '@rollup/plugin-node-resolve';
import commonjs from '@rollup/plugin-commonjs';
import babel from '@rollup/plugin-babel';
import peerDepsExternal from 'rollup-plugin-peer-deps-external';
import { glob } from 'glob';
import path from 'path';

export default {
  input: 'src/index.js',
  output: [
    {
      file: 'dist/index.js',
      format: 'cjs',
      sourcemap: true
    },
    {
      file: 'dist/index.esm.js',
      format: 'esm',
      sourcemap: true
    }
  ],
  plugins: [
    peerDepsExternal(),
    resolve(),
    commonjs(),
    babel({
      babelHelpers: 'bundled',
      exclude: 'node_modules/**',
      presets: ['@babel/preset-env', '@babel/preset-react']
    })
  ]
};
```

## 6. Create Babel Config

Create a `.babelrc` file:

```json
{
  "presets": ["@babel/preset-env", "@babel/preset-react"]
}
```

## 7. Create Your Index File to Export All Icons

```javascript
// src/index.js

// Dynamically import and export all icon components
const iconModules = require.context('../icons', false, /\.js$/);

// Export individual named exports for each icon
iconModules.keys().forEach(fileName => {
  const componentName = path.basename(fileName, '.js');
  const component = iconModules(fileName).default;
  exports[componentName] = component;
});

// For backwards compatibility, also export an object with all icons
const allIcons = {};
iconModules.keys().forEach(fileName => {
  const componentName = path.basename(fileName, '.js');
  allIcons[componentName] = iconModules(fileName).default;
});

export default allIcons;
```

If you prefer a more static approach (which might work better with tree-shaking):

```javascript
// src/index.js
// Import all your icon components
import Icon1 from '../icons/Icon1';
import Icon2 from '../icons/Icon2';
// ... more imports

// Export components individually
export { Icon1, Icon2 /*, ... */ };

// Also export as a default object for convenience
export default {
  Icon1,
  Icon2,
  // ... more icons
};
```

## 8. Create .npmignore File

```
node_modules
src
icons
.babelrc
rollup.config.js
.gitignore
```

## 9. Build and Publish

```bash
npm run build
npm publish
```

## Using Your Package

Once published, users can use your icons in different ways:

```jsx
// Import all icons
import Icons from 'my-react-icons';

function App() {
  return <div><Icons.IconName /></div>;
}
```

```jsx
// Import specific icons (better for tree shaking)
import { IconName1, IconName2 } from 'my-react-icons';

function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <IconName1 />
      <IconName2 />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Advanced: Type Definitions (Optional)

If you're using TypeScript or want to provide type definitions:

Create a file `index.d.ts` in your `src` directory:

```typescript
import { FC, SVGProps } from 'react';

export interface IconProps extends SVGProps<SVGSVGElement> {
  // Any additional props your icons accept
  size?: number | string;
  color?: string;
}

// Declare each icon component
export const Icon1: FC<IconProps>;
export const Icon2: FC<IconProps>;
// ... more declarations

// Default export with all icons
declare const Icons: {
  Icon1: FC<IconProps>;
  Icon2: FC<IconProps>;
  // ... more icons
};

export default Icons;
```

Then update your package.json:

```json
{
  "types": "dist/index.d.ts"
}
```

And configure Rollup to copy the type definitions to the dist folder.

This setup gives you a complete and flexible way to share your React icon components as an NPM package!
