# Fixing the Missing Icons in Your Built Package

Let's troubleshoot why your icons aren't being included in your build and fix it:

## 1. Check Your Generated index.js

First, let's make sure your index.js file is actually importing and exporting the icons correctly:

1. Open your `src/index.js` file
2. Verify that it's correctly importing your icon components
3. Make sure that both named exports and default exports are set up

If you're using automatic generation, make sure the generation script is working correctly.

## 2. Manually Create a Simple index.js for Testing

Create a simple version of your index file with explicit imports for testing:

```javascript
// src/index.js
// Import a couple of icons explicitly for testing
import IconOne from '../icons/IconOne.js';  // Use an actual icon name from your collection
import IconTwo from '../icons/IconTwo.js';  // Use an actual icon name from your collection

// Export individually
export { IconOne, IconTwo };

// Export as default object
export default {
  IconOne,
  IconTwo
};

// Add console.log for debugging
console.log('Icons loaded:', IconOne, IconTwo);
```

## 3. Update Rollup Config to Include Icons

Make sure your Rollup configuration is set up to include your icon files:

```javascript
import resolve from '@rollup/plugin-node-resolve';
import commonjs from '@rollup/plugin-commonjs';
import babel from '@rollup/plugin-babel';
import peerDepsExternal from 'rollup-plugin-peer-deps-external';
const glob = require('glob');

export default {
  input: 'src/index.js',
  output: [
    {
      file: 'dist/index.js',
      format: 'cjs',
      sourcemap: true,
      exports: 'named'  // Add this to handle named exports properly
    },
    {
      file: 'dist/index.esm.js',
      format: 'esm',
      sourcemap: true
    }
  ],
  plugins: [
    peerDepsExternal(),
    resolve({
      extensions: ['.js', '.jsx']  // Make sure to resolve these extensions
    }),
    commonjs(),
    babel({
      babelHelpers: 'bundled',
      exclude: 'node_modules/**',
      presets: ['@babel/preset-env', '@babel/preset-react']
    })
  ],
  // Explicitly tell Rollup to preserve modules
  preserveModules: false,
  // Tell Rollup to be verbose about warnings
  onwarn: function(warning, warn) {
    // Print all warnings
    console.warn(warning.message);
    // Continue with default warning handler
    warn(warning);
  }
};
```

## 4. Check Your Icon Component Structure

Make sure your icon components are properly structured and can be imported:

```javascript
// Example of how icons/IconOne.js might look
import React from 'react';

const IconOne = (props) => (
  <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" {...props}>
    {/* SVG path data here */}
    <path d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2z" />
  </svg>
);

export default IconOne;
```

## 5. Add Debug Output to Build Process

Add a script to check what files are being processed:

```bash
# In your terminal after build
ls -la dist/
cat dist/index.js | grep -A 5 -B 5 IconOne
```

## 6. Use a Different Build Approach with Rollup

Try a more direct approach with Rollup:

```javascript
// rollup.config.js
import resolve from '@rollup/plugin-node-resolve';
import commonjs from '@rollup/plugin-commonjs';
import babel from '@rollup/plugin-babel';
import peerDepsExternal from 'rollup-plugin-peer-deps-external';
const glob = require('glob');

// Get all icon files
const iconFiles = glob.sync('./icons/*.js');

// Create a multi-entry config
export default [
  // Build the index file
  {
    input: 'src/index.js',
    output: [
      {
        file: 'dist/index.js',
        format: 'cjs',
        sourcemap: true
      },
      {
        file: 'dist/index.esm.js',
        format: 'esm',
        sourcemap: true
      }
    ],
    plugins: [
      peerDepsExternal(),
      resolve({
        extensions: ['.js', '.jsx']
      }),
      commonjs(),
      babel({
        babelHelpers: 'bundled',
        exclude: 'node_modules/**',
        presets: ['@babel/preset-env', '@babel/preset-react']
      })
    ]
  },

  // Build each icon individually to make sure they're included
  {
    input: iconFiles,
    output: {
      dir: 'dist/icons',
      format: 'esm',
      sourcemap: true
    },
    plugins: [
      peerDepsExternal(),
      resolve({
        extensions: ['.js', '.jsx']
      }),
      commonjs(),
      babel({
        babelHelpers: 'bundled',
        exclude: 'node_modules/**',
        presets: ['@babel/preset-env', '@babel/preset-react']
      })
    ]
  }
];
```

Then update your index.js to import from the dist/icons directory:

```javascript
// This generates the index file that imports from the built icons
const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');
const glob = require('glob');

// Get all icon files
const iconFiles = glob.sync('./icons/*.js');
const iconNames = iconFiles.map(file => path.basename(file, '.js'));

// Generate imports referring to the built versions
const imports = iconNames.map(name => 
  `import ${name} from './icons/${name}.js';`
).join('\n');

const namedExports = `export {\n  ${iconNames.join(',\n  ')}\n};`;
const defaultExport = `export default {\n  ${iconNames.join(',\n  ')}\n};`;

// Combine everything
const fileContent = `${imports}\n\n${namedExports}\n\n${defaultExport}\n`;

// Create the file
fs.writeFileSync(path.join(__dirname, 'src/index.js'), fileContent);

console.log('Index file generated successfully');
```

## 7. Check the Built Files

After building, check your `dist` directory to see what files were created:

```bash
ls -la dist/
```

If you see the index files but no icon files, there's definitely an issue with your Rollup configuration.

## 8. Testing Your Package Locally

You can test your package locally without publishing:

```bash
# In your package directory
npm pack

# This creates a .tgz file
# Take note of the filename, e.g., my-react-icons-1.0.0.tgz
```

Then in your test project:

```bash
npm install /path/to/my-react-icons-1.0.0.tgz
```

This will install your package locally, and you can test if the icons are actually accessible.

